    "extras": [
      "Use a contactless Visa or Mastercard with OVpay and always tap in and out on every train, tram, metro, or bus ride.",
      "Anne Frank House needs mandatory advance booking 6–8 weeks out; Van Gogh Museum is best booked 2–4 weeks ahead.",
      "The I Amsterdam City Card 48-hour option is about ₹8,280 and covers GVB transit, Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk, and a canal cruise, but not the Van Gogh Museum.",
      "Keukenhof is seasonal only from mid-March to early May; if you are travelling then, use the Haarlem day for tulip fields and the combi-ticket instead of a standard city day.",
      "Museumkaart is about ₹6,900 and starts paying off fast if you are stacking Amsterdam and Utrecht museums, but it does not cover Van Gogh Museum or Keukenhof.",
      "If you want one more heavyweight art stop, use Rotterdam as a base for a 25-minute Den Haag day trip covering Mauritshuis, Escher in Het Paleis, and Scheveningen."
